      "description": "Offering a mechanically robust E46 M3 featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six, equipped with individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing. This example utilizes the desirable ZF 6-speed manual transmission to send power through a variable M differential lock. The suspension geometry remains precise, featuring a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup that provides exceptional lateral grip and chassis feedback. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and subframe reinforcement, ensuring the structural integrity matches the powertrain's performance. A true enthusiast's machine that prioritizes throttle response and handling dynamics.",
